cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software, please cite it as below."
title: "Collaborative Hill Lab"
abstract: >-
  A reproducible laboratory for whether LLM agents can build shared truth
  under mixed incentives. Extends Tcaci & Huyck's N-person Iterated
  Prisoner's Dilemma work (pairwise vs neighbourhood interaction structures)
  to LLM-agent populations over evidence, provenance, and institutions.
authors:
  - family-names: Tcaci
    given-names: Cristian
type: software
version: 0.1.0
date-released: "2026-07-13"
repository-code: "https://github.com/Chris0Jeky/collaborative-hill-lab"
keywords:
  - multi-agent systems
  - large language models
  - cooperation
  - social dilemmas
  - N-person prisoner's dilemma
  - epistemic commons
  - reproducibility
license: MIT
